str2: (Hebrew), Joanna, Johanna, wife of Chuza, Herod's steward. Feminine of the same as Ioannes; Joanna, a Christian.
A woman, wife, my lady. Probably from the base of ginomai; a woman; specially, a wife.
Compound of heros and eidos; heroic; Herod, the name of four Jewish kings.
From epi and tropos; a commissioner, i.e. Domestic manager, guardian.
Chuza, a steward of Herod Antipas. Of uncertain origin; Chuzas, an officer of Herod.
Susannah, a woman of the retinue of Jesus. Of Hebrew origin; lily; Susannah, an Israelitess.
(a) of two: another, a second, (b) other, different, (c) one's neighbor. Of uncertain affinity; other or different.

str2: From diakonos; to be an attendant, i.e. Wait upon (figuratively) teacher; technically, to act as a Christian deacon.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
From out, out from among, from, suggesting from the interior outwards. A primary preposition denoting origin, from, out.
